        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 4:06PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 406 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southwest of Kim, or 31 miles northeast of Des Moines, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kim and open country along and south of highway 160.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
